Pt vaccinated with HIB-titer 6 months post immunization, child dx w/ HIB disease. Fever of 105 and could not walk. Admitted to hosp w/Pneumonia, body rash & his eyes were swollen shut. Blood culture were + for HIB disease.
LAB_DATA: Spinal Tap - OK; Sedimentation rate 89 day of admission. 72 day of discharge. Anemic

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt vaccinated with HIB-Titer  vomited 7 times became pale, lethargic, & listness. Seen by MD, temp 101, HR 160, & quite lethargic. Hospitalized for observation.
HISTORY: At 5 1/2 mo, had shaking spells that lasted10-15 sec. Also had a possible head lag referred to a pediatric neurologist.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt vaccinated with HIB-Titer became very lethargic, limp & pale. Afebrile, had rapid heart beat & was taken to ER;
Pt vaccinated with OPV developed fever, diarrhea & anorexia; Unable to walk because of lt leg paralysis. Polio Type II confirmed
LAB_DATA: Type II poliovirus isolated from Stool specimen collected 20AUG90. Specimens were submitted to the CDC for wild vs vaccine strain determination. Immune Globulin results available

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt vaccinated with OPV developed urinary symptoms, unable to walk, lower extremity pain, hospitalized paralysis ascended to chest causing respiratory distress; facial involvement.
LAB_DATA: Spinal Tap - WBC 48, Glucose 57, Protein 46, MRI - r/o possible tumor - negtive titers, stool & throat cultures pending.
HISTORY: Child received chemotherapy for Leukemia. Child received 2 doses of ORIMUNE as an infant, since dx w/leukemia.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt vaccinated with Heptavax-B developed urticaria, swelling all over her body, wheezing, bronchiolitis.
Pt vaccinated with HIB-Titer developed hives over entire body. Two wks later, hives still persist.
HISTORY: Mother of child allergic to themerosol.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3 days /p vax given bright red hard lumps involving the lt leg were seen, office notes states injection was given in the rt leg.  Office notes record this as an injection site reaction.
/P vax pt has lipoatrophy of the buttocks.  His mother feels this is getting larger, size on 11Jun90 was 20 X 15mm.  Depression at injection site only.  No other symptoms.
2 wks following DTP/OPV vax, child developed hives which have persisted on & off for 2 mon.  Dermatologist suggested that hives might be due to vax since no other cause was found.
Received OPV/DTP vax & next day developed hives. Low grade fever, child looks fine otherwise.

At 2 mo. old infant received DTP, 6 hrs later developed blueness & pallor of face, generalized weakness, lasting 30 min. to 1 hr, @ 4 mo. old received DT/OPV, 8 hrs later, again dev. blueness & pallor of face & gen'l weakness for 20-30 min.
LAB_DATA: EEG was done on 15May90 for rule out seizure which showed normal EEG.
